.\" heirloom-port-uninstall(7)
.TH HEIRLOOM-PORT-UNINSTALL 7 "2026-07-02" "Heirloom Darwin port" "Port ALM"
.SH NAME
heirloom-port-uninstall \- reverse an install using the recorded manifest
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B make uninstall
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads
.I .install-manifest-\fIpkg\fP.txt
and removes every listed file and symlink. Refuses to proceed if the
manifest is missing (there is no safe way to know what to remove) or
if the manifest contains any path outside
.IR PREFIX .
After the file / symlink removals, empty directories under
.I PREFIX
are pruned.
.PP
The manifest itself is left in place after uninstall for audit trail.
Remove it by hand if desired.
.SH SAFETY
Refuses to run when the manifest is missing. Refuses paths outside
.IR PREFIX .
Never touches
.IR /System ,
.IR /usr ,
or any Homebrew-managed path.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .install-manifest-\fIpkg\fP.txt
Consumed input. Written by
.BR heirloom-port-install (7).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Uninstall complete or nothing to remove.
.TP
.B 1
Manifest missing or contains paths outside
.IR PREFIX .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR heirloom-port-install (7),
.BR heirloom-port-status (7)
